Game Instruction

Create a Tic – Tac -Toe game that allows a player to play against a computer. 

Game details 
Tic Tac Toe is bassically a two man game where you try to beat your opponent be marching
three boxed out of nine provided boxes, and the other tries to block your move while 
trying to beat you too.

Requirements
[X] 1. There should be a welcome view that shows a welcome, statement, the game 
instructions and gives the user a choice of playing with X or O against the computer.

[X] 2. The tic-tac-toe game should be played on a grid that’s 3 squares by 3 squares.
[X] Add an event to each of the boxes that when clicked it should show (x,o)

[X] 3.There should be a way to display ‘win’ for the first player who gets 3 of her marks 
in a row (up, down, across, or diagonally).

[X] 4. When all 9 squares are full, and no player has 3 marks in a row, the game should end
 in a tie.

[X] 5. If a player wins or the game ties, there should be a way to play again or reset the 
game.

[X] 6. There should be a way to keep track of the scores between a player and the computer.

